<H1>The Explosion of the Ariane 5</H1></CENTER>
<P>On June 4, 1996 an unmanned Ariane 5 rocket launched by the European =
Space=20
Agency exploded just forty seconds after its lift-off from Kourou, =
French=20
Guiana. <IMG height=3D117 alt=3D"Ariane explosion" hspace=3D15=20
src=3D"http://www.ima.umn.edu/~arnold/disasters/ariane.jpg" width=3D289 =
align=3Dright=20
vspace=3D10> The rocket was on its first voyage, after a decade of =
development=20
costing $7 billion. The destroyed rocket and its cargo were valued at =
$500=20
million. A board of inquiry investigated the causes of the explosion and =
in two=20
weeks issued a report. It turned out that the cause of the failure was a =

software error in the inertial reference system. Specifically a 64 bit =
floating=20
point number relating to the horizontal velocity of the rocket with =
respect to=20
the platform was converted to a 16 bit signed integer. The number was =
larger=20
than 32,767, the largest integer storeable in a 16 bit signed integer, =
and thus=20
the conversion failed. </P>
<P><!-- The report of the Inquiry Board is available <A=0A=
HREF=3D"http://www.esrin.esa.it/htdocs/tidc/Press/Press96/ariane5rep.html=
"=0A=
>in English</A> or <A=0A=
HREF=3D"http://www.cnes.fr/actualites/news/rapport_501.html">in the=0A=
original French</A>.=0A=
The following paragraphs are extracted from that=0A=
report.=0A=
-->The=20
following paragraphs are extracted from <A=20
href=3D"http://www.ima.umn.edu/~arnold/disasters/ariane5rep.html">the =
report of=20
the Inquiry Board</A>. An <A=20
href=3D"http://www.around.com/ariane.html">interesting article</A> on =
the accident=20
and its implications by James Gleick appeared in The New York Times =
Magazine of=20
1 December 1996. The <A=20
href=3D"http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/9606/04/rocket.explode/">CNN article =
reporting=20
the explosion</A>, from which the above graphics were taken, is also =
available.=20
</P>
<P><CITE>On 4 June 1996, the maiden flight of the Ariane 5 launcher =
ended in a=20
failure. Only about 40 seconds after initiation of the flight sequence, =
at an=20
altitude of about 3700 m, the launcher veered off its flight path, broke =
up and=20
exploded. </CITE></P>
<P><CITE>The failure of the Ariane 501 was caused by the complete loss =
of=20
guidance and attitude information 37 seconds after start of the main =
engine=20
ignition sequence (30 seconds after lift-off). This loss of information =
was due=20
to specification and design errors in the software of the inertial =
reference=20
system. </CITE></P>
<P><CITE>The internal SRI* software exception was caused during =
execution of a=20
data conversion from 64-bit floating point to 16-bit signed integer =
value. The=20
floating point number which was converted had a value greater than what =
could be=20
represented by a 16-bit signed integer. </CITE></P>
<P><FONT size=3D-1>*SRI stands for Syst=E8me de R=E9f=E9rence Inertielle =
or Inertial=20
Reference System.</FONT> </P>
